<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-06-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-06-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="223" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Pike</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 103.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-06-08"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 8, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 20th ultimo (No. 87)
                            relative to the question of the Scheldt tolls, to the Polish
                            insurrection, and to the impression produced by General Banks’s
                            movements, has been received and perused with much interest.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your most obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">James</hi> S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Pike</hi>,
                                Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c</hi>., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                                    &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>